Example 1. Creating a basic dumbell plot

## Load libraries
suppressPackageStartupMessages({
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2) 
library(rlang)
library(utils)
library(data.table)
library(dumbbell)

     
})



## Generate Some Random Data

z<-data.frame(Group = c(rep("A",10),rep("B",10)),
              Subject = c(paste("sub_",1:10,sep=""),paste("sub_",1:10,sep="")),
              result = c(sample(1:100000, 20, replace=T)),
              analysis = c(rep("a",5),rep("b",5) ,rep("a",5),rep("b",5) )
              
)

## Create 2 groups "Fresh", "Thawed"

b<-z %>% filter(Group == "A")
c<-z %>% filter(Group == "B")

b$Subject<-as.factor(b$Subject)
c$Subject<-as.factor(c$Subject)

d<-merge(b,c, by.x=c("Subject", "analysis"), by.y = c("Subject","analysis"))


## Order by delta
e<-d %>% mutate("diff"=pmin(result.x-result.y)) %>% arrange(diff)
d$Subject<-factor(d$Subject,  e$Subject)


##Create a basic dumbell Plot
dumbbell(xdf=d,id = "Subject",key="analysis",column1 = "result.x",column2 = "result.y",
         lab1 = "labelA",lab2 = "labelB")

Example 2. Adding a delta column

## Adding a delta column
dumbbell(xdf = d, id = "Subject", key = "analysis", column1 = "result.x", 
    column2 = "result.y", lab1 = "labelA", lab2 = "labelB", delt = 1, 
    expandx = 0.1)

Example 3. Adding values as labels

## Adding values as labels
dumbbell(xdf = d, id = "Subject", key = "analysis", column1 = "result.x", 
    column2 = "result.y", lab1 = "labelA", lab2 = "labelB", pt_val = 1, 
    expandx = 0.05, col_lab1 = "blue", col_lab2 = "red")

Example 4. Adding arrows

## Adding arrows
dumbbell(xdf = d, id = "Subject", key = "analysis", column1 = "result.x", 
    column2 = "result.y", lab1 = "labelA", lab2 = "labelB", expandx = 0.01, 
    arrow = 1, pt_alpha = 0.6, arrow_size = 0.2, segsize = 0.7, 
    pointsize = 1.5, col_seg1 = "#A9A9A9", col_seg2 = "#A9A9A9")

Example 4. Adding facets

## Adding facets
dumbbell(xdf = d, id = "Subject", key = "analysis", column1 = "result.x", 
    column2 = "result.y", lab1 = "labelA", lab2 = "labelB") + 
    facet_wrap(analysis ~ ., ncol = 1, scales = "free")

Example 5. Adding facets and pvalues (Wilcox.test paired)

## Adding facets
dumbbell(xdf = d, id = "Subject", key = "analysis", column1 = "result.x", 
    column2 = "result.y", lab1 = "labelA", lab2 = "labelB", pval = 1) + 
    facet_wrap(analysis ~ ., ncol = 1, scales = "free")

Example 6. Mixing it up

## Adding facets, highlight one direction, add arrows and the
## delta value
dumbbell(xdf = d, id = "Subject", key = "analysis", column1 = "result.x", 
    column2 = "result.y", lab1 = "labelA", lab2 = "labelB", delt = 1, 
    col_seg2 = "red", col_seg1 = "blue", arrow = 1, pt_alpha = 0.6, 
    pointsize = 2, expandx = 0.3, segsize = 0.5, textsize = 2, 
    pval = 1) + facet_wrap(analysis ~ ., ncol = 1, scales = "free")
